<div class="collapse" id="procedure">
    <div>    
        <p>The process begins by assessing whether or not a licence application is required and can be obtained.</p>
        <p> This is followed by gathering the necessary information, which can take time especially for group organisations or those with a long operating history.</p>
        <p> Once the information is obtained, the relevant forms, supplements and documents are prepared and submitted to the SFC along with necessary fees. </p>
        <p> Upon receipt of the application, it is common for the SFC to seek further information either through written or telephone queries. The entire process for standard appications usually takes between 3 and 4 months from the date the application is submitted.</p>
    </div>
</div>

